>> Changing the LEAF would be a red-flag that the call should be 
>> monitored and fed to the Skipjack backdoor. 
>But you can only tell that the LEAF has been monitored *after* you try the 
>escrowed keys and discover that they don't work.  Not much of a red flag...

Well, without using the escrowed keys, the FBI could look at the Unit ID in
the LEAF.  If a) the Unit ID isn't an issued one  or b) the Unit ID changes
every time the phone is used, this would be very suspicious.

